						               													<description>This is a supplement to Contemptible Little Armies: Third Edition &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#147; World War I Era: Fast Play Wargame Rules 1910-1928. It includes some historical background, army lists, a simple campaign system, special characters and new optional rules for terrain and weather specific to warfare in Central Asia from 1919- 1926.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The armies in the lists represent historical forces as well as a few &amp;ldquo;what ifs&amp;rdquo;. They include: Bolsheviks, the &amp;ldquo;Army of God&amp;rdquo;, White Russians, the Army of Baron Ungern-Sternberg, Chinese Warlord Armies, Chinese Chinghai Fontier Armies, Chinese Bandits, Mongolian Tribes, Tibetans, Ngoloks, Basmachis, the Afghan Army, Central Asian Bandits, the Army of British India, the Turkish Army, the Japanese Army, and Dinosaur Hunters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The book has 41 single sided pages that are cerlox bound with a plastic cover on the front. There are a couple of black and white photos within and one map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Contemptible Little Armies: Third Edition &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#147; World War I Era: Fast Play Wargame Rules 1910-1928&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
